From: Christophe JAILLET <christophe.jaillet@wanadoo.fr>
Date: Sun, 9 Aug 2020 22:34:06 +0200
Subject: drm: amdgpu: Use the correct size when allocating memory
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit
Git-commit: 78484d7c747e30468b35bd5f19edf602f50162a7
Patch-mainline: v5.9-rc2
Alt-commit: 5068ed578e34450a285fca3f9d830361b44267ad
References: jsc#SLE-12680, jsc#SLE-12880, jsc#SLE-12882, jsc#SLE-12883, jsc#SLE-13496, jsc#SLE-15322

When '*sgt' is allocated, we must allocated 'sizeof(**sgt)' bytes instead
of 'sizeof(*sg)'.

The sizeof(*sg) is bigger than sizeof(**sgt) so this wastes memory but
it won't lead to corruption.

Fixes: f44ffd677fb3 ("drm/amdgpu: add support for exporting VRAM using DMA-buf v3")
Reviewed-by: Christian KÃ¶nig <christian.koenig@amd.com>
Signed-off-by: Christophe JAILLET <christophe.jaillet@wanadoo.fr>
Signed-off-by: Alex Deucher <alexander.deucher@amd.com>
Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Signed-off-by: Patrik Jakobsson <pjakobsson@suse.de>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_vram_mgr.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_vram_mgr.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_vram_mgr.c
index 134cc36e30c5..0739e259bf91 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_vram_mgr.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_vram_mgr.c
@@ -462,7 +462,7 @@ int amdgpu_vram_mgr_alloc_sgt(struct amdgpu_device *adev,
 	unsigned int pages;
 	int i, r;
 
-	*sgt = kmalloc(sizeof(*sg), GFP_KERNEL);
+	*sgt = kmalloc(sizeof(**sgt), GFP_KERNEL);
 	if (!*sgt)
 		return -ENOMEM;
 
